# Pytest Conventions

## Config reference
From `pyproject.toml`:
- `asyncio_mode = "auto"` — all async test functions run automatically, no `@pytest.mark.asyncio` needed.
- `testpaths = ["backend/tests"]`

## Test file placement
Mirror the source tree inside `backend/tests/`:
```
backend/pipeline/engine.py
backend/tests/test_pipeline/test_engine.py

backend/ingest/reader.py
backend/tests/test_ingest/test_reader.py

backend/api/routes/health.py
backend/tests/test_api/test_health.py
```

## Naming
- Test files: `test_<module>.py`
- Test functions: `test_<behavior_under_test>` — describe the scenario, not the method:
```python
# ✅
async def test_intake_blocks_malicious_input(): ...
async def test_execute_read_returns_truncated_when_over_limit(): ...

# ❌
async def test_intake_node(): ...
async def test_execute_read(): ...
```

## Async tests
Because `asyncio_mode = "auto"`, just write `async def test_...`. Do not add the `@pytest.mark.asyncio` decorator:
```python
# ✅
async def test_pipeline_runs_to_end():
    ctx = PipelineContext(job_id="test-1", settings=test_settings, ...)
    result = await run_pipeline(ctx)
    assert result.frames["output"] is not None

# ❌ — redundant decorator
@pytest.mark.asyncio
async def test_pipeline_runs_to_end(): ...
```

## Fixtures
Prefer narrow, explicit fixtures over broad shared state. Put shared fixtures in `conftest.py` at the test root:
```
backend/tests/conftest.py            # shared fixtures (client, test_settings, fixtures_dir)
backend/tests/fixtures/              # test data files (CSV, etc.)
```

## Mocking external services
Mock at the boundary interface, not deep internals. Use the ABC/Protocol as the mock spec:
```python
# ✅
mock_ds = MagicMock(spec=DataSource)
mock_ds.read_frame.return_value = pl.LazyFrame({"col": [1, 2, 3]})

# ❌ — mocking internal file system methods
mock_path = MagicMock()
mock_path.open.return_value.__enter__.return_value.read.return_value = "..."
```

## Run commands
```bash
uv run pytest                        # all tests
uv run pytest backend/tests/test_api # one test directory
uv run pytest -x                     # stop on first failure
uv run pytest --cov                  # with coverage
```
